Usage: create_pg_cover_cell [-help] -box {x1 y1 x2 y2} -cell <string>
                            -lef_file <string> -routing_layers <string>

-help                        # Prints out the command usage
-box {x1 y1 x2 y2}           # specifies the box of PG cover cell
                             # (box, required)
-cell <string>               # specifies the PG cover cell name
                             # (string, required)
-lef_file <string>           # specifies the LEF file name that will be saved
                             # of the PG cover cell. The CLASS of the cell is
                             # COVER (string, required)
-routing_layers <string>     # specifies the layers that reserved for PG
                             # routing including the cut layers (string, required)